<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the depths of the pandemic in 2020, a lot o=
f people were stuck at home with nothing to do, so they started trading sto=
cks. This made the pandemic less boring=C2=A0for them. But they also starte=
d=C2=A0<em>talking=C2=A0</em>a lot about trading stocks, which made the pan=
demic much=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</em>boring=C2=A0for their loved ones. Here i=
s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30143722.279526/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9yb29raWUtdHJhZGVycy1hcmUtY2FsbGluZy1=
pdC1xdWl0cy1hbmQtdGhlaXItZmFtaWxpZXMtYXJlLXRocmlsbGVkLTExNjcyNTEzMjcyP21vZD=
1pdHBfd3NqJnJ1PXlhaG9v/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3c79d3ba" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a funny =
Wall Street Journal story</a> about a musician named Alan Garcia, who durin=
g the pandemic=C2=A0 stopped getting gigs and started trading stocks, but w=
ho has since gotten better:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The obsession didn=E2=80=99t end when he sat d=
own in the living room with his wife, Adriana Rodriguez, each evening. For =
about two years, he talked about investing. Mr. Garcia, a 34-year-old Houst=
on resident, even started watching investing videos in bed at night.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CHe was here,=E2=80=9D Ms. Rodriguez s=
aid, =E2=80=9Cbut he wasn=E2=80=99t here.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In early 2022, Mr. Garcia lost everything in h=
is portfolio on a bad options bet, leaving him in a foul mood. But the next=
 morning, he felt relieved. After Ms. Rodriguez, a lawyer, left for the off=
ice, he worked on his music all day instead of checking the market. He hasn=
=E2=80=99t traded on the app since.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ms. Rodriguez is thrilled. Mr. Garcia agrees i=
t is for the best=E2=80=94mostly, anyway. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ve never been=
 this good in our lives,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9COne day I=E2=80=99ll ge=
t that $2,000 back though.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A basic idea of the Boredom Markets Hypothesis=
 is that trading stocks is just not intrinsically=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>f=
un. A society in which everyone is trading stocks for fun is a society wher=
e the opportunities for fun have severely atrophied. When your musician hus=
band gets back to making music instead of watching YouTube videos about opt=
ions day-trading, that=E2=80=99s good for you and the world, even if it is =
bad for your bank account and the options market.</p>
